values:
&nbsp;today was interesting. got my arse up to go run, so that i could get back to the house before baseball boys got here, because i get red-faced and sweaty and very unattractive when i work out. thankfully i made it. so then i showered and came back out to help clear the porch so the boys [q, kyle, jeff, and george]&nbsp;could paint the front of the apartment.&nbsp;there were various pieces of wood [unused trim, flooring, etc] piled haphazardly around, providing an ideal habitat for creepy crawlies. 

thus begun the great spider hunt.&nbsp;

besides lots of teensy, relatively harmless spiders, there were at least 5 black widows,&nbsp;along with at least 4 egg sacks. ich ich ich.&nbsp;&nbsp;because i am a complete pansy about spiders in general, and deadly ones in particular, i made sure i was well protected. namely, soccer socks and my knee-high mucking boots for to protect my little toesies. and so i became the spider stomper with much flailing and 'eee'-ing. i'm sure it was an amusing sight.&nbsp;

it was actually kind of fun though. i ended up spending more time with the guys today than i have before. me and cody went to lunch with them [fresh-air bar-b-q, yum yum] and i got to talk to them a good bit. discovered that i actually really like q- he's fun/easy to talk to and honestly smarter than i had initially thought. so now i feel bad for presuming. still a fan of george, though a little of the 'oo, shiny' has worn off. although, i think he's greek [or half? his mom is from what i can tell] which is pretty hot. i mean, he's a new yorker through and through, but i can see the greek in his features now that i know that's what it is. and greek boys are often quite pretty. yum.&nbsp;;)

anyhow. i should be going. need to get into bed earlier tonight so it's easier to get up in the morning. the guys are coming again, probably for the last time, and my folks will be gone a little before they get here, so i need to&nbsp;make sure i'm back from my run and&nbsp;not in the shower. night, lovelies!

&nbsp;had to go to the dentist this morning since i haven't been in a while. usually hate the dentist because i almost always have at least one cavity, although often more like 2 or 3. annoyingly, my little brother, who eats more sugary sweet things than me and doesn't always remember to brush, has never had a cavity. where i was gifted with my mother's bad teeth, he got dad's perfect teeth, the brat. held true today as well and i'm going back to get my one cavity treated tomorrow. one bonus for today was that i didn't get the red-headed devil-woman technician.&nbsp;she's actually really nice, but she is vicious&nbsp;[or 'diligent,' as mom likes to say]&nbsp;&nbsp;with those pointy scraper things. i always end up with a headache when she's through. but i got the nice blonde lady today, so my mouth doesn't completely hate me.&nbsp; 

have now not gone running in two days- yesterday because i got up at 7.30 to help mom with horses out at leslie's [which takes at least 2-3 hours] and this morning got up at 7 for my 8 o'clock appt. and now i've got another appt in the morning, so that might screw me up as well. thinking i'll&nbsp;might try to go this evening, or at least get up tomorrow before my appt and go, since it's at 9.10 instead of 8, so long as i leave myself time to shower. shall see.&nbsp; 

hmm. what else? no progress with baseball&nbsp;boy, because i am chicken shit and can't say anything. besides, if he's leaving in a week or two&nbsp;what's the point? besides getting over my ridiculous shyness. meh. anyhow, i think the division tournament is going to be hosted here, since right now the pirates are winning it, so at least there's a few more games for me to watch him. although i sometimes like the games that he doesn't play better, because then he's sitting out by the field and there's more potential for interaction. a couple of my friends came out last weekend and both agreed that he looks over towards me a lot, although with them there, it could have been for a different reason, because sarah and tegan are both really pretty. but i like to hope i was still part of why he was looking over. :) 

gonna go check on the horses and look at the paint samples we've got up in the house. might go see a movie at the $2 theater later with sarie. otherwise, it's laundry and chores today. fun times.
